runProcess

public int runProcess(java.lang.Object pParam,
                      PipelineResult pResult)
               throws java.lang.Exception
This method loads the CostCenter objects from the OrderRepository into the Order object. It does this by constructing a new CostCenter instance based on the class mapped to the repository item type of the CostCenter. It then iterates through the properties listed in the loadProperties property inherited by this class, setting the values in the object. This method requires that an Order, order repository item, and OrderManager object be supplied in pParam in a HashMap. Use the B2BPipelineConstants class' static members to key the objects in the HashMap.

Specified by:
runProcess in interface PipelineProcessor
Parameters:
pParam - a HashMap which must contain an Order, order repository item, and OrderManager object
pResult - a PipelineResult object which stores any information which must be returned from this method invokation
Returns:
an integer specifying the processor's return code
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - throws any exception back to the caller
See Also:
